Of all the people who are aware of my existence, and who know me on campus, the one who I think understood me the best is you. I always loved having conversations with you. Talks which were not often but always were refreshing and refueling. Thank you Anu for being here, and always sharing your thoughts with me. The exchange of ideas between us, added more value to it. I hope to learn more from you and have even more wonderful time together. We'll stay connected.. No need to say. ‚ù§

To dear RVM, I hope your overall IIT Experience was good enough. It is ok to have both positive and negatives in life (and IIT), for the balance. I hope you learned something from this. Thoda to jor se bol liya kro, saamne wala guess hi krta reh jayega. Mumbai se bahar aao or bahar ki duniya bhi dekho, or ha challenge dhyan rkhna.....vrna ghnta hi sunai dega.

Dear Devanshi, 
I found you during the hardest moments of my life, you have always been there for me. I will miss our non-sensical conversations over long walks and dinner, I'll miss our obsession with random spaces in the campus, and with the stars. You can always count on me for accompanying you to random shady places. Also, thanks for giving me validation for every strange things I do and say- be it making a deformed piece during our pottery sessions. Glad to found you! I wish you all the best for the upcoming years, and I hope you achieve great success :)

Dear Khushboo,
You're an amazing amazing friend with a beautiful soul and heart. Conversations with you are wholesome, warm, and easy-going. I wish you all the best for your future :)

Dear Mamta,
You're a person with great humor, being with you has always made me laugh. I will never forget the days when we used to go to Beauki's terrace and sing random old hindi songs. I will miss you a lot, always stay in touch momo. All the best for your future :)
Lots of love.

Dear Hyma,
I will always remember me knocking at your door randomly, and talking about random stuff. I will miss our video calls and the non-sense things we used to talk about, mimicking people- instead of focusing on our online group presentations. I still remember you being there for me during my first Quarantine. Thanks for clicking my aesthetic random portraits. Thanks for accompanying me every place, and for every thing I asked for.

Dear Shirisha,
You are genuinely the most humble person I've ever some across, I will miss playing badminton with you and having chai with you. Yes things went a little haywire, but you have always been a lovely person and very strong, with a very amazing poem writing skills, I hope you become a very famous poet someday and break all the patriarchal structures. Cheers to an amazing soul, one who's obsessed with sunshines and dance. 
All the best for your future, always keep smiling and jumping as you always do. 
Love you Shirisha. Always. :)
Aarthi you have handled all the obstacles gracefully, kudos for that!

Dear Padosan,

I cannot imagine 3rd and 4th semester without you. You have been my alarm, my loudest supporter, my breakfast partner and my hype woman. You have given your shoulder for me to cry on several times. You are always ready to do the most random thing, laj sharam toh hai hi nahi tumme; I love that! It has been fun to do crazy shit along with you. Mujhe kuch senti likhna hai but kya hi likhu, tujhe sab pata hi hai. Bas ek baar dil se shukriya for being you, your presence made my masters fun.

- Praneeta

I remember the phone calls to each other in 1st semester, being scared of the transition from biology. Rote rote kr hi liya bro. Hope you get whatever you wish for in life.

- Praneeta

My first and forever friend in IIT Gandhinagar. I am going to miss your ghr ka khakhra and tasty tasty nashta. Thank you for always being there when I need you and making me feel good. Going to miss our endless talks so much. Stay connected!!

Simran I was so scared to talk to you in the 1st semester, kaafi intimidating lagi thi mujhe but bhai sahab tu toh dev maanus nikali re. You are dope.

- Praneeta

Dear Ritu,
First of all, best wishes for your dreams, future challenges, and achievements. When, the first time I saw you, I decided not to talk to you and not to make you a friend. But as time passes, we become closer and more closer. You have a key to unlock any opportunity; just use it wisely and positively, the rest of the thing automatically happens. Like someone says, ' if some reaction develops slowly, take long time it will end up with a valuable product. 
So, let's start with your unpredictable mixture of SUKH-DUKh.
I think this equation describes you better.
2 (Pagalpan- Dioxide) + 6( Cheerful-Nitrate)  + 3( Multi-Talent-Chloride)  + ( Dukhi-Cyanide) + 4 (Caring-Kindness-Carbonate) ======  RITU (Product) + 500 (Memories) KJ + 600 (Happiness) KJ
Ye equations balance karke rakhna throughout your life, and keep me updated with new methods, catalysts and byproducts.
 I will miss long walks and tumari der sari baate, itni saari ki kya batau. dukhbhari kahaniya, or bhi jane kya kya.
You are a brave woman with a veryy kind heart. Who trusts anyone, or no one, who cares about anyone or no one. So, Basically, you are a performer, sometimes top and less time bottom.
Again thanks for being my friend in my very hard time, asking me for food, caring. or Baki baate hoti rahengi :)
Ajay
The "Papaji" for MJ and Lava. You made any situation bearable and made it seem like an easy task

Dearest Abhinanda,
It won't be an exaggeration if I say that I survived this place because of you. From organizing events, sharing trauma experiences, walking countless miles to getting trolled together - our friendship has unlocked a quite diverse and representative list of achievements. Your rants against poetry and introverts will be engraved on my heart forever. Feeling so content to see your conversion into a poetry person. Will keep sending prayers so that you keep acing (hopefully not in the way I'll be acing mine ;)) in your academic and personal life, insha'Allah. Couldn't be more grateful to have found you. Dosti bani rahe. xD

Dearest Meeta,
This might be the last letter that you'll receive as a member of fellow social class. No, this letter couldn't have been started without mentioning our crucial middle class bonding. We came to this place with our similar apprehensions and fears of not being able to fit in. We found comfort in sharing our anxieties with each other over countless sessions of chai. Somehow we made through it all and dear lord did we learn major life lessons. Aisey hi mera naam raushan karti raho kyunki "ag laavaan majboori nu, aan jaan di pasoori nu!" May you have the least possible number of Bojack-days in your life or none. Ameen. Zindagi rahi toh phir milenge.

Love,
Beenish.

My dear brother Sakib,
You are the most amazing person I have ever met. Always teasing you was the nicest part of our time together at IITGn. I'll never forget you waking me up in the middle of the night. Every time you bothered me, I wanted to beat you, yet you know you are my heart.

Dear Shraddha,
Needless to say that you're our very own Picasso. :) Will always cherish the beautiful art sessions we've had in these years. Thank you for always getting my jokes, haha. (:p) Please stay as compassionate as you are and as thoughtful as you can be. So grateful to have met you. Sending you all my prayers and best wishes.

Love,
Beenish.
When we join an institute, there is a person we call our first friend. He was the one for me. Never seen someone like him, did whatever he wanted to unapologetically. The special one.
Sabko kandha dete dete akhir me aapko bhi kandha mil hi gya, haste raho hamesha jaise har baat pe has dete ho.
Baba aapke ke kya hi kehne , byah kar lena bsdk

Dearest Apoorva,
It all started with bonding over not wanting to work for neuroscience assignments and look where we are now. Not very far literally but maybe figuratively, lol. The best thing about befriending you is that it's always so effortless being around you, in a good sense. You make the other person feel very comfortable with you so quickly and with such grace, haaye. One of the highest compliments I think I've received here is that we look alike (god knows how though). It must be apparent with all this fangirling that I really like you. :") I'll tell you why. Not many people I've met in my life are good at texting and replying to memes appropriately. Especially the extroverts, ugh. It's really a pleasure knowing you (and it's all mine). Hope you get everything good in life and more. 

Love,
Beenish.

Dear Aadishree,
It's difficult to not connect with someone you share similar anxieties with and it's even more difficult to not connect with someone you share your interests and (almost)hobbies with. So you see, it was easy connecting with you. The editor in you might spot some mistakes in this message but please ignore, haha. Hope we become more confident in our skin, more flexible in our attitude and more resilient with life's uncertainties. Hope you find all the strength and courage to handle your fears. Hope you stay as pun-y as you are, hope to read your book soon. To hope and inspiration! :")

Love,
Beenish.

Dear Madhu,
Thank you for giving your best in sailing this sinking boat of our pandemic batch. CR-ing must have been a pain if not worse. We didn't spend too much time together or talked very often but it was nice whenever we did. I hope you get to go on more solo/non-solo trips, eat best biryaani and do whatever you love. Best wishes ahead.

Love,
Beenish.

Pyaari Khushi,
From our shared interest in penguins, extensive cooking sessions, not going for meals together to forming SPC to continue not meeting each other - we have brilliantly procrastinated our way to come a long way in our friendship. May we keep snapping out of our unhealthy routines as and when required. May we stop enabling each other at some point, lol. Meal buddies who have troubles with having meals in the first place. I must say that I learned a lot from you like how I am incapable of owning plants on my own and should never be trusted with one. I hope you keep writing your high-ly-famous-tales. Sending all my prayers and best wishes for your upcoming life ventures. :")

Your neighbor-to-be,
Beenish.

Dear Tanisha,
I remember it all started with cat videos and since then we've come a loong way but I think that a substantial part of our relationship is still cat videos (as it should be!). :") I love how we rarely talk and still seem to get along pretty well. Not to mention the important role of BI trauma in solidifying our bond, lol. But I seriously hope to see you pioneering in the field someday (that is only if you wish). To more cat content and other escape tricks! To learning more healthy coping mechanisms (more cat content or better, real cats :p)! Prayers and best wishes. :")

Love,
Beenish.

Dear Wardah,
I love this nice feeling of our shared identity which only holds true if one comes from the wrong side of the political spectrum. It is a Schr√∂dinger relationship (couldn't help it lol) that we share. It's as real as it isn't, it depends. Anyway, I just wanted to tell you that I absolutely love how you are everything I could never be and yet so relatable. You certainly have enriched my perspective. I hope you taada-taadi get to wherever you want to be in life and pray for your well-being.

Love,
Beenish.

Dear Divya,
I am glad that we finally got to spend some time together on campus. It has been nice knowing you. Sending prayers and best wishes for your future plans.

Love,
Beenish.

Dear Jeeva,
I don't think I have complimented you enough about your beautiful hair, masha'Allah. The moment you started critiquing Meenakshi Sundareshwar with such passion, I knew that you are very cultured, haha. Would have loved to talk to you more but I keep getting in my own way of socializing with new people, ugh. Anyway, sending prayers for your career and future plans. Best wishes ahead.

Love,
Beenish.

Dear Alpha,
I really appreciate your meme taste and love your reel-making skills. I could have told you this in-person but that wouldn't have been the approved introvert way. ;) It has been a pleasure knowing you and barging into your room at almost midnight (that one time), haha. Dearest Tortoise,
Dino wants you to explore as many mountains (both literally and figuratively) as it is humanely possible. Sending all my prayers and colorful flowers as my parting gift to you, something you can keep forever. May our bond keeps growing stronger with each cute/sad/emo reel we send in each other's DM. It is time for the-bold-and-the-bang gang to take over the world! Will always be rooting for you. Miss me. :")

Love,
Dino.

People call you little flower and we all have seen you blossom in the masters, which was bound to happen considering how the thesis semester went. Quoting Monica from Friends "Welcome to the real world. It sucks. You're gonna love it." Aside from all this, you have a killer music choice, keep it up.

P.S. I hope you have finished reading one hundred years of solitude :-D,

- Praneeta

Wangshu 1st semester me mujhe laga tha ki I would spend my whole masters without talking to you but that has changed and I get to see ki tum toh bahot hi sahi bande ho (Pehle bhi pata hi tha, but I had this perception of you as someone having their shit together and like fully serious and now I have also seen your fun side). The most memorable days for me were when Abhi, Uzma, You and I posed for photos as fuckbois, kaafi maza aaya tha us din and also when you made pasta for us wo din toh honestly mere liye kaafi fun tha, I am glad I did not miss that! Hope to have more days where you cook for us.

- Praneeta

I think every time I think of you Khushi, I always think of the times you have fed me. Humesha kuch na kuch khilaati hi rehti hai, you are good host; keep it up.

P.S. The fact that we both know the full routine of Gal mithi mithi bol should actually come in use to us someday. 

- Praneeta

Uzma, in this terrifying world, all we have are the connections that we make.

With this line in mind I think you were the first genuine connection I made in IIT. We understand each others' story and we know what makes us the person we are. I can write about drinking chai with you and all the fun stuff but more importantly during those chai meetings, I felt seen and I hope you did too.

You have been a genuine friend, and I hope you keep up creating a space for yourself in all the future endeavours you take.

Tumhari chai partner
Praneeta

Shraddha, you are the artist of the group. Bahot hi helpful insaan hai, sabke birthday pe kuch na kuch picasso waale kaam kiye hai tune. Aage bhi life me continued rakhna. Ek funny memory thi jab tum mere aur Uzma ke liye chai leke aayi thi aur tumko humne "Chotu" nickname de diya tha, I think usko continue krna tha but khair koi na. Apna dhyaan rakhna!

- Praneeta

Dearest Simran,
It has been strangely reassuring knowing you through different kinds of down times we've had in this place (can't remember many ups, lol). From fasting together in ramadan to crying together over thesis, we braved it all. Hope you soon get to go to France and live your life. Hope it's mostly ups from here on. Will be looking forward to listening to more playlists curated by 'bohemian broccoli' and reading more pieces written by 'generalzucchini'. You always inspire me. My heart fills with prayers for you. Hope you find peace and contentment in life. Hope you get to enjoy frequent rain and nice breeze, always. Take care of yourself, stay queer. xD  

Love,
Beenish.

"It's the 6th of May, 2019 as the email from the Amalthea arrives in my inbox, I was already declared as the core member and this new email tells me that the events coordinator is - you. The instant I had a look at the email, I knew that the events at Amalthea were going to be excellent when you were there to lead them, I never really got a chance to know you before that, but a preexistent respect, a pre existent belief in your sincerety, in your leadership and more importantly in your support already existed, and the next 3 years would prove all those initial thoughts to be true.
